rComments: She's very enthusiastic about history, really nice and understanding. History 100  was a bit hard because it isn't  your typical history class, it focused a lot on methods and  citations, etc.  The T.A. does most of the grading and its a bit tough but manageable. Haven't gotten my final grade yet but I am aiming for a B. Lots of assignments!

This course covered such a broad range of history; it would have been easy for someone to loose the interest and attention of the class.  Visuals helped lectures a lot.  Again, I'm very surprised at the clarity of the course given the range of subjects.  She's quite an intelligent person.
Very unclear about her expectations. Her midterm seemed poorly planned and very ambiguous. Her paper topics are not very critical in nature but she expects critical responses.
So far so good! Her lectures are clear and as a prof shes very helpful and understanding. The way she presents the material  is challenging in a good way. Must go to every lecture!

Clearly presented information and identified expectations for midterms and final. Writing assignments were engaging and challenging. Leads very beneficial discussions that help to grasp the material. Maya is there for her students if they ever need her. Fantastic Professor! Highly recommended!!!
